Hello there!
ð¸ð¸ð¸ I think it's the right time to say HELLO to our followers out here ð
My name is Anastasia Ivanova, I live in Sydney, Australia, I have my family (my hubby and 2 little monkeys) and my favourite businesses @paperforcuties (bright decor for bright events) and @SydneyPaperFlowers (WOW paper flowers)
Today there are 5 facts about me "Where I am from"))
1) I was born in a small village near Kazan in the center of Russia and spent there all my school years. There is a great river Volga in 10 minutes walk from my parents house. Then I moved to the city as a big Uni girl ð¤
2) My hubby took me to Saint-Petersburg  as this was his school years city and he dreamed to come back there one day
3) Later on we decided to relocate to Moscow as we've got a secrect dream which we could realise most likely from there.
4) After 5 years living in Moscow we got our dream come true - we got permanent visa to Australia ð¦ðº and moved to Sydney
5) Today we enjoy our life here in Down Under (yes, it is that far!) and I can't stop ð± getting requests in my Etsy shop from US guys asking for a paper flower wall to hire this weekend in.... for example California, US ð
I do not know what will be our next destination.
But I enjoy my TODAY here!

What makes me happy today?! Well being engaged to someone in the military isn't easy, especially while my fiancÃ© is away on tour of duty. I miss him so much, he's the person I spend my days with and he fills my life with happiness! So why am I happy he's away?? I started thinking about how easy it is for us to speak, we call and FaceTime every day and message throughout the day and I am so thankful for that! Many couples didn't get that chance years ago, they went months without contact, without knowing if they were okay, I can't imagine that! Let's talk about how your weight hinders you from doing things you REALLY want to. How many of you have something you always wanted to do but haven't because you were afraid or your weight inhibited you from doing it?? I have. I love traveling. I specifically remember as my seat belt kept getting closer to the end of no return. âï¸ I remember when I never even owned a pair of jeans for years because shopping for a size 24 seemed impossible. ðI remember thinking I will never get married because who would love me when I didn't love myself? Yep. REAL EMOTIONS. Deep right? Well, I can guarantee that at least 1 out of the 32,000 people that are reading this have felt these same feelings. I have been there. I have felt what you have felt. I never imagined I could lose all that weight again. But, I did. I mentally had to change. I had to realize I was worth it. I deserved more. I wanted more. And one year later, I can say without a shadow of a doubt that every painful, happy, stressful, hard, and depressing moment was worth it. You can do it too. You just have to believe in yourself first... #transformationtuesday #transformation #weightloss #weightlossjourney

While planning a wedding (either as a bride OR as a professional), we tend to get so swept up in all the details and traditions of a wedding that we never stop to think about the why. Why in the world do we exchange expensive rings? Or cut a cake? Or carry a bouquet? Before you spend thousands and thousands of dollars, shouldn't you understand exactly what you are doing and why you are doing it? We think so! And for that reason we are going to be sharing some fun and unique facts about the history of wedding traditions. Be sure to follow along over the next couple of weeks to learn more about where these crazy customs came from! "Eric knew I had always wanted to go hot air ballooning, so one day he told me he found this "amazing Groupon deal" for a hot air balloon ride in Napa. It was for a Friday, so he suggested we might as well make a weekend out of it too! Little did I know, there was no Groupon deal and that was just his way of getting me to block off the weekend without being suspicious. So we go to Napa, and Eric had scheduled some wine tastings for after our hot air balloon ride. We got to the first winery where we had a private tasting. The lady then took us "on a tour of the grounds".. Where she led us up to a beautiful patio. I noticed there was a table with champagne set for two, and then she left. That's when I knew what was happening. I started bawling with the first word that came out of his mouth! As if that wasn't enough, he secretly had both of our families come in from all over California, and we were all staying the weekend in a beautiful ranch house overlooking wine country. And to top it all off, we went "wine tasting with the family" the next day-- only to be surprised at the winery by forty of our closest friends! It was the most magical weekend ever :)"

My beautiful boy! Warning! Super sappy post that I wanted to share with you all. I feel like we are still in the honeymoon phase. I miss him all the time and still get sad when he goes to work even though he's been doing it for the past year plus of our marriage. Marriage was difficult for me to adjust to but am so grateful for the struggles we went through in the beginning. This man right here makes my world make sense and I'm so proud to be his. So excited to love on him and serve him for the rest of my life. We have so many plans, not sure if we will get to them all (live in Italy, own a tiny house, own a farm, live on the sea, scuba dive the deep cold waters, lobster hunt), but thrilled to be able to go through them with him. It's really, really easy to get caught up in the fanfare of a wedding. The dress, the cake, the planning and the pressure to put on a perfect day for everyone. It's easily understandable how we may lose sight of the real reason for the celebration. 
In the end...our wedding day will be just that. Our wedding DAY. It will only last for 24 hours and soon after that all of the months of planning and preparation will soon be forgotten. Life will go back to, virtually, the same as it was before. 
I'd be lying if I said I wasn't excited for September 10th. I'd be lying if I said I haven't put a lot of work into making it a memorable day for the both of us. I've put a lot of pressure on myself to do everything perfectly. But has everything gone as planned? No!

The truth is that I could, honestly, marry Ivo in a paper bag in the pouring rain and still be over-the-moon happy. And while I'm happy to jump through all the hoops and do the planning I'm always reminding myself of this. Our wedding day is about Ivo and I. No one else. As long as he is there I am happy. And I'll think this forever and always throughout the course of forever. As long as he is there... I will be happy.

Save the dates are my jam - just call me the Save the Date Queen. Just kidding. @theideaemporium should have that title. She should have every creative title because she is the shit (no other way to say that.) Awhile ago, we had a little heart to heart about invites and I promised to show you Scott and I's save the dates for our October wedding. Here they are. 
Scott and I opted to have 2 save the dates: one for our siblings, family and bridal party and one that was paper based and still amazing for our other amazing guests. These stole our hearts. 
I am crazy. I will be the first to admit it. I push limits and boundaries and I stride for unique elements. Carey (God) made my vision come to life with laser printed luggage tag, a custom microfiber lining with our wedding website AND a custom box with our engagement picture printed on it. I mean, I just can't. I have one of these bad boys on my counter just to stare at. 
Save the Dates start the mood for your wedding day and they are the first way to build the excitement for your wedding day. They can be as simple as paper or a magnetic picture, or as elaborate as a snow globe (I have seen a few of those). When designing your save the dates, make sure it:
A. Capture your personality
B. Showcase the mood for your event
C. Make sure it is mildly informative
D. Have fun with it!! What are you doing for your save the dates?

"Our long distance relationship story began on a cold winters night in early 2013. He remembers me constantly bumping into his hand (I wanted him to hold my hand but I was too shy to say so!) Later that year he had to go back home and our skype calls began. I love getting old school mail from him. It's especially exciting when he tells me to go check the mail and I get a thoughtful card. First ever....Tips & Tricks Tuesday! Every Tuesday I'm going to share tips and tricks all about the wedding industry.  Hi there! I'm Olivia owner of Olivia Gird Photography. I've been photographing weddings for the past 13 years and I'd love to share all of my experience with you!  Tip: When planning your engagement session, always have a plan B. I book many couples months (even years) in advance and often they are traveling from out of town. Many local venues and private estates will allow hourly rentals for a nominal fee. This local botanical garden was a great plan B as it poured for most of this couples session. Having your summer party indoors? Make sure to bring everything people love about the season while enjoying the A/C! ðâï¸ 1) Keep the palette bright - we used pops of green & blue at this Bar Mitzvah, as well as natural grass on each food station & passed tray. 
2) Use airy elements, like this beautiful flying buffet, to help the room feel uncluttered and open, like the outdoors! Space furniture in groupings wide apart to keep things clutter-free when the crowd arrives. 
3) Lighting is key! Nothing makes you feel more trapped indoors than a dark room or horrible fluorescent overheads. Turn warm lights up, keep the cool colors along the walls, and use spots & pin spots to make sure there's none of that horrible just-stepped-inside squint. 
4) Hire EELA so you can enjoy your night!! A great tip any season and occasion ð

#TakeoverTuesday Tip: The Great Outdoors

1. When you can, offer both indoor and outdoor options for your guests so they can choose whether to be outside or not. This is especially important if you have elderly or pregnant guests.

2. If you're having many outdoor components, make sure you offer your guests the essentials: water, sunscreen, and mini fans, whether electric or paper. Also, can't hurt to communicate ahead of time that you'll be providing these so people aren't scrambling to bring their own.

3. Choose furniture wisely. Always be ready for rain, and keep in mind that metal can heat up quickly. Water repellant fabrics and seat cushions can make for a drier, more comfortable experience for everyone in these cases.

Now that Danielle and Stephen have shared the news, I can post a a photo of their engagement this past weekend. Just clicking through the images, looking for one to share, had me smiling and even a little teary eyed as I remembered the moment.

I could not be any more excited and happy for these two. They are great together, they are so loving and supportive, they are friends and partners, they are each others right kind of weird (who doesn't love that Dr. Seuss quote??). And witnessing the emotion of that moment, as Stephen dropped to one knee, the surprise on Danielle's face, was so special.. it's hard to adequately put into words. 
I'm honored to have been a part of it with them. And I will definitely have a blog post to share soon but, for now, here's a little sneak peek!

Sure, we as photographers can all learn and grow on our own. We can watch tutorials. Practice our posing. Read all of the books on lighting and composition. All in the quiet of our home. But when you get down to it, shouldnât we be helping each other? Learning from each other? Giving advice to your fellow photographer about their light meter? Their SEO? Their innate ability to relax and pose clients? So often photographers feel the need to hide all of their secrets, their ways or their ideas. But truly, arenât we all better together? We say yes! Better Together Savannah is a gathering of creatives that want to learn, play, style, laugh and shoot all while building a creative community. Will there be a teacher? Yes. We all will be. The two-day event will take place August 1-2 here in Savannah complete with two fully styled shoots, styled by the talented @tzneedham. Join us for this incredible #communityovercompetition event here in the dreamy city of Savannah!

This picture deserves it's own post. It came up on my Facebook feed that it was 3 years ago today. I remember when my friend posted it and I cried. I knew I had let myself go. I knew that I had lost all motivation. I was on crutches and non weight bearing for 3 whole months after shattering my lower leg and having surgery. This was the highest weight I ever got to. I have lost ð«80 POUNDS ð« since this picture. It took me ONE YEAR. Even after seeing this picture it didn't motivate me to change. It made me feel more hopeless. I had to be ready. I had to mentally get my head in the game. Unfortunately, it took my mom dying to realize that. Even after I started my journey I still debated and argued with myself if I I could do it for 3 whole months. I wish there was magical potion or some pill that I could tell you worked. But, unfortunately it's 80% diet, 20% working out, and 100% mental. Never again. I'm never going back. Mentally I'm changed. Mentally, I decided to do it for myself. Every single day I make that decision. It's #transformationtuesday and this was the beginning of mine. #transformation #weightloss #weightlossjourney

One of my favorite things to design is the rehearsal dinner invitation to coordinate with a custom invitation suite. If the groom's parents are hosting, it gives me an opportunity to get to know them a little bit and to include them in the wedding design process, and even if they're not, it's always fun to design an additional piece that still feels special enough to be an event invitation but doesn't take away from the main invite. For this May wedding in the blue ridge mountains, P+T opted to go with an ombre blush invitation, picking up the blush color from the sky of the invitation to keep it simple and elegant and to give a nod to the pink sunset under which they would be dining with their closest friends and family the evening before their wedding.

After an incredible anniversary weekend, Nate and I came home and FOUGHT! It's amazing how surprising and humbling marriage can be. After we sat in a discouraged silence for some time following our discussion, Nate suggested we read our 'messages in a bottle'. These are little notes that our loved ones wrote to us at our engagement party. We have three bottles: First Fight, 1st Anniversary and First baby. We had gone through the first fight notes within a week or so of coming home from our honeymoon last year. I was so thankful that Nate remembered these last night. He shook the notes out of the anniversary bottle and had me read them aloud. Some were funny, some were serious but they all spoke to each of our very tender hearts. These reminders of love brought us back to a place of reconciliation with each other. One even said "have sex even if you fight because of expectations" I had to laugh(not because it talked about sex) but because it was exactly what I needed to hear. It made me feel like we were normal and that it was to be expected that these newly married people would end up fighting about expectations. This is a perfect example of why we need community. If you know someone who is getting married soon, this is an amazing blessing to give them.

Hello my loves,

Let me introduce you to myself. My name is Michelle and I am a wedding and portrait photographer on Bostonâs North Shore. I am located in downtown Beverly and absolutely love life.

So let me tell you all about myself.. I am a maker, creator, lover of light, kittens, and all things organic. I am heavenly inspired by the world, the ocean, my family, and I am incredibly passionate for creating images.

I have a passion for meeting people, laughing until it hurts, traveling and trying out all new things, reading, and always exploring. I am the type of person who needs to push the boundaries of expectations, seek, and live life to the edge. I am an explorer and living life in love and to the fullest is the only way to live.

With that being said, I cannot thank my incredibly supportive family, friends, clients and the incredible support system at the #risingtidesociety for all the inspiration this year. You are all so amazing. I love you all!

Drop me a line in the comments. Hit me up and follow us on SnapChat @michellebehrexo and make sure to like our page on Facebook at www.facebook.com/michellebehrephotography

Troy knows that I am pretty good about figuring out surprises, so making this work without me finding out was something to be proud of! The night before he asked, he told me the next morning we would be having brunch with his coworkers by the beach. I woke up the next morning and got ready by the time he told me we would have to leave. When I went to put on my outfit, he stopped me and said "Actually, I think you should wear that white dress you wore to Easter. It looks pretty on you." I told him I thought that was too fancy for a casual brunch, but he assured me that his coworkers would be dressed nice too. Without a second thought, I put it on and we went out the door. When we got to the beach, he said we had some time first since we were early. So we were walking on the shore and all of a sudden he had me turn a corner...there was a blanket laid out with a dozen roses, candles, letters from him, wine glasses, and seashells scattered. I immediately started to tear up as he got down on one knee and asked me to marry him and be his forever. I said yes, of course!! It made me even happier to hear that he asked my Dad already too. Off to the side I eventually noticed one of my closest friends who had been hiding and taking pictures and video. The beach is our favorite place and so special to us. I always envisioned and hoped deep down that he would ask me there. He followed our proposal with horseback riding and dinner in Laguna Beach. I can easily say it was the best day of my life! â¤ï¸ Via @wedding.proposals

Monograms can be confusing!  A rule of thumb I like to follow is this, only use combined monograms (couple's first initial on either sides of their last name initial) on stationery pieces being used AFTER the ceremony.  Why?  Because the couple is not yet married when save the dates and invitations are sent, a combined monogram is not accurate.  If the monogram style is something you'd like to incorporate, consider using only first initials on pre-wedding pieces. .

Cynthia and Ben were married on the coldest day of the year in New Haven, CT on February 14, 2016.

It was -30Â°. With wind. 
It was so cold we could barely breathe and if left outside in the wind one would quickly succumb. Talk about exciting! The story was definitely one of the most fun wedding stories I've ever written. The bride flew me up three days before the wedding so that I would have a chance to really get to know her family which I did and I adore them all. They actually feel like one of my own family mrmbers now. 
Because of awesome couples like this, all of the sacrifices I've made to make this company work are worth every tear, every drop of blood and sweat.  Well, maybe not blood-- I don't think I've ever actually bled but I definitely have cried and sweated for this adventure.

5 years ago today had just failed a test for a job in the Army (a HUGE blessing in disguise) and I was upset. He asked if I still wanted to go to Disneyland and I said, "sure. it's better than sitting at home being upset." And boy am I glad we went. 5 years ago I went to Disneyland in the morning as Nick's girlfriend and I left the park that night as his fiance. 
Disneyland will forever hold a special place in my heart. It's where he dropped down on one knee. The cast members made time stand still, blocking off a section of the park, having a photographer capture the moments, and then setting off the castle bells when I said "yes!" (it was more like "omg shut up! yes! shut up!" haha. 
My life started with Nick on this day 5 years ago. He joined the Army. We've been separated for months on end due to training. We've moved from California to Alaska to Virginia. Rescued 3 dogs together. Had a baby. Are having another baby. We close on our first house at the end of this month and then will undergo all the fun of renovations. 
There's no one in the world I'd rather do life with and I'm so glad he asked me to do life with him June 7th, 2011.

There's no way around it. You gotta work HARD for it. 
How many of you are like me and have fallen for it? 90 days to be ripped then you can stop. Stick a needle in your chin and your self confidence skyrockets. 21 days and then you can go back to eating crappy. We all know that puts a bandaid on a stab wound. 
You get healthy by working HARD, making sacrifices, and keeping your deep WHY as a priority. That's the reason why my clients see their life change. 
When I start them out, they know this is NOT a quick fix. Healthy a lifestyle. This is hard work. And that's why we work tirelessly every day to keep each other in check. 
It's the accountability piece that keeps us going. There are GREAT workout programs everywhere! But the one thing that I pride our groups on is the daily accountability to keep going- the support- the call outs- the nutrition support. 
Getting healthy is HARD work. There's no way around that. And I'm damn proud of our challenge groups for being a great example of that every day! Ain't that right Janiece, Lynn, Lisa, Kate, Nicole!? How about you? How do you do with accountability?

This morning, I woke up engaged to the man of my dreams. Sitting out back reflecting on how blessed I really am and what in the world did I do to deserve it? I only dreamed of Matt. The most selfless, loyal, faithful, generous hard working man I know.  The list goes on. Our relationship has been filled with laughter ,passion, yelling, love, God, faith, adventure, prayer, highs and mild lows. We've ALWAYS had each other's backs, that's for certain. Not a day goes by that this man doesn't make me laugh and let me know how much I am loved. Everything he does, he always has me in mind. The way he looks at me, priceless. If you're close with us, you know. We aren't perfect but pinch me because sometimes I feel like life with him isn't real. So needless to say, I am over flowing with love, emotion and gratefulness to have found something not everyone finds in life, true love. Cheers to us Matt, my forever best friend. Kelly's & Huy's wedding was inspired by modern art and architecture. They picked the uber #modern @slsbeverlyhills as their reception venue and went with a predominantly white and grey palette with blocks of bright colors throughout. We went with all long tables, and the centerpieces mimicked Kelly's bouquet. Some tables had runners of rainbow flowers and others had trios. There must have been 80 vases in total, but you can see that the #reception was still minimal and stark white to keep it modern. This was one of my favorite weddings of my career. She is beautiful.

"Jon and I love to explore. We were driving to San Diego to have dinner with my mom for Mother's Day. A few hours early, Jon suggested we visit La Jolla Shores and walk to a place where they have hidden tree swings that overlook the ocean. Since the swings were a "secret," we searched the coordinates and started to make our way. What was supposed to be a 5 minute walk turned to a 45 minute hike up a hill (in my high heels)!Once arrived, I saw the disappointment on Jon's face to find they had recently taken the swings down. But that didn't stop him from finding a tree shaped like a bench up on top of the cliff where we sat and took in the beautiful sunset over the water. It was there that we reflected on how much of a blessing our relationship had been and at the perfect golden hour, Jon got down on one knee and asked, "Will You Marry Me?" And to that I followed with "Of course!""
-
Story by @lindsayobello

Does #money make us #happy?

This was a concept discussed in the Documentary âHappyâ which I watched recently and I want to share with you a little nugget that I took from the movie. 
Based on the research that they did when filming this #documentary they found again and again that once the basic human needs had been met financially (e.g. Water, food, shelter and clothing) that money no longer played a role in contributing to peopleâs #happiness, in fact in most countries the more money people had the more #depressed they were because they were on something referred to as the hedonic treadmill. The Hedonic Treadmill also known as hedonic adaptation, is the observed tendency of humans to quickly return to a relatively stable level of happiness despite major positive or negative events or life changes. In other words as people become more #wealthy and accumulate more assets (i.e. the white picket fence, range rovers in the garage and kids in private school) they become accustomed to this new level of perceived #wealth and continue to want more and more.

According to the Happy Documentary these are the things they found to be the keys to happiness and longevity: â¢ #Play â physical exercise
â¢ New experiences
â¢ #Friends and #family â being part of a #community
â¢ Doing things that are #meaningful â being #engaged
â¢ #Appreciating what we have â #gratitude

These are all big things that my good friends @MarcusPearce and @DamianKristof speak of on their podcast #100NotOut

I highly recommend to everyone that they watch this documentary (only $5 for HD rental on Google Play) and download some 100 Not Out podcasts.

It's wedding week!! That means that this time next week I'll be this 18 year old cutie's wife. Being a wife in itself is a special joy. It means that you found the one person in the world who you chose to spend forever with. You weren't forced with that person or born into their family. You made the choice out of love to travel through forever with your one. And if you're really lucky, like myself, you'll also spend forever wondering how the heck you got so lucky. Over the past 7 years my Kyle has traveled with me through teen years and beyond. Young silly love that made me late to class more times than I can count from too much lovin' in the commons. 1) Get a temporary wedding band that is slightly larger, since your fingers might be swollen.

2) Keep some ginger candies or chews handy in case you feel sick. 
3) Ask your caterer to prepare a special menu for you excluding foods you shouldn't eat, and with the foods your craving!

4) Always factor in a few sizes up when dress shopping. Since it typically takes about 4-6 months for a dress to come in, your belly will be larger by then. If you're not showing yet during your first appointment, let your consultant and alterations department know you're expecting, that way they can also factor in a few inches during fittings. 
5) Hire a wedding planner! Your hormones are raging and you're probably pretty emotional. You don't want to lose your cool due to the stress of wedding planning. Hire a planner who will take care of all the nitty gritty and make sure that the process is as perfect as can be for you and your fiancÃ©.

UNDERGARMENTS! Why?  They hold your breasts up off your rib cage which give your torso a more longer, slimmer look. Also, fits your body's shape to the dresses shape resulting in less alterations. Also helps keep your posture straight preventing unwanted slouchy , droopy pictures.  If your planning on wearing something "special" for him under your dress, I suggest waiting and freshen up at the end of the day. Change later after your reception. You will be hot and even possibly sweaty, give him a more fresh you! Bridal Exclusives has a few options to choose from! I knew every detail of Benjamin's graduation party yesterday. Because well.. I helped meticulously plan it for months. I designed and handmade the invitations, I made a few of the decorations, I sifted through photos and photos to put on display and in the slideshow, I even taste-tested the sweets to be served ð ð¬ð­
But no way, no how, did I have any inclination of the sneakiness of this man. That midway through, he would turn this grad party intended for him into a celebration of us. And what he said to me was "Its never just about me" Ringing in my heart as a reminder that we've endured a 6-year-long relationship more challenging than even our closest friends and family could understand at times. In some seasons, people thought we were torturing ourselves by remaining together. But the truth of our love and faith is that from the beginning we were commissioned to be a team, and we (with Jesus as our head coach) will always be a team #TeamGenBen

happiness is a journey, not a destination. for a long time it seemed to me that life was about to begin - real life. but there was always some obstacle in the way, something to be gotten through first, some unfinished business, time still to be served, a debt to be paid. at last it dawned on me that these obstacles were my life. this perspective has helped me to see there is no way to happiness. happiness is the way. so treasure every moment you have and remember that time waits for no one.

Sooo I'm going to be marrying my best friend â¤ I thought I'd tell you a little bit about him.

My best friend waits for hours in the lobby of my office, just so he can see me for a few minutes when I get out of work if I'm having a long day. He wakes up early and travels miles to bring me a sleepover bag he's packed when I lose my suitcase on weekends away. 
He brings me sunflowers when I've had a busy day and haven't had a chance to go out and see the sun. He brings me flowers, just because. 
He helps me draft, re draft and proof read applications for secondments even if we are on holiday. He is patient with me when I am running late, and I am always running late. He rummages through bins for me (don't ask), he encourages me, prays with me,  fights for me, advises me, surprises me, listens to me, cares deeply for me. He gives and gives and gives, and continues to give even when he receives nothing in return. He dreams BIG dreams with me and doesn't settle for mediocrity. He works hard, damn hard. He laughs with me, cries with me, crazy dances when the moment's right with me. 
He is there for me. Always. 
That is my fiance, I could go on and on.

I had been walking with blinders on the night I met Rich. A friend took me out to the local country bar, trying to get me out of the house. After a few drinks I spotted a tall, handsome, tattooed stud of man. Apparently he had seen me too cause we kept looking over to see one another. Me being the shy girl I am, would look away when I'd get caught staring at him. Liquid courage set in and I followed him to the bar where we later danced and exchanged numbers. From that moment on, we have been stuck like glue. A little over two years later Richard had taken me for a walk in my sister in laws orchard. Down one of the rows of almond trees was a long rose petal lined isle with mason jar lanterns lighting the way to a candle lit table full of pictures of us and Thomas Rhett's "Die a happy man" playing in the background. Overwhelmed with joy, the tears started to flow. He got down on his knee and asked me to make him the happiest man in the world. Oddly, the only words I could muster were... "oh my God, shut up!!" No idea why, but that's what came out. Shortly after however, I said YES!!! Needless to say we are now on our way to happily ever after! June 10th 2017â¡â¡â¡â¡ #afloral #engaged #summerlovin

So inspired by Beauty @bubbyandbean & her journey with feeding 2 of her children. As mom's we know just breastfeeding 1 child can be a lot for us, so to be one baby #2 is wonderful! She will be sharing her journey. â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢â¢#Repost from @bubbyandbean While pregnant with Emmett, I was much more confident about the prospect of breastfeeding than while I was pregnant with Essley, because of the obvious (I'd done it before, for 18+ months) - but when he was born, we faced a different set of challenges. Now that we're 5 months in and well into our groove, and I can genuinely say (once again) that there is little I love more than the precious, intense, extraordinary experience of feeding a baby. I'm getting personal over on the blog today (link in profile) and sharing the details of my breastfeeding journey with babe # 2 - including the struggles and triumphs, who has been the most supportive, my favorite breastfeeding products (like the @Ergobaby nursing pillow you see in this pic), and why I hope to continue to nurse for as long as I did with my first. I spent my entire life dancing and a large portion of my life teaching others to dance for various reasons. From health and wellness to technique to surprise dances. You name it, I've been in demand for all kinds of different styles. Having such passion to teach what I love most and sharing this God given talent has opened my creativity to keeping each dance unique and special in their own way. Bringing out each of my students' personality through movement to make it special and perfect for them...and I often caught myself imagining what it would be like to see my idea of the perfect first dance for me to come to life...and it was never quite clear...so today, for the first time ever, Kevin and I shall move in sync with one another...together, creating and designing our perfect first dance. Today, we also celebrate Kevins fathers birthday, expressing our love and passion through strategic movement for the very first time. #happybirthdaycraig #ilovemyfuturefatherinlaw #thankyougodforeverything #blessedbeyondwords #danceislife #firstdance #movement #loveofmylife #ifoundmydancepartner #hesmyeverything #ourlovestory #engaged #4monthstogo #idoforever #excited #happiestgirlintheworld #savethedate #godisgreat #ourstoryismyfavorite #k&k #pinedoschmadwedding #idreamedofthisday #dreamscometrue #keepdreaming #keepgoing #keepdancing  #danceyourheartout #adanceyouwontforget #halfmoonbay #hmb photo by @lize147

And so today, it seemed only appropriate to write a letter to the love of my life for all that he has done for me these past few years (link in bio) ð Chris and I went out to celebrate last night because this is a week full of joy- a week that sybmbolizes the end of the hardest 10 years of my life. And though we know my life will never go back to normal, we also count our blessings. Because we also know it could have been so much worse. And no matter how hard life gets, it is so, so very precious. Always. And I will be forever thankful for the chance to experience something in this life that has drawn me ever more tightly into the loving arms of Jesus. "And as Your mercy falls
I will raise my hands and praise
The God who gives and takes away... And I will praise You in this storm
And I will lift my hands
For You are who You are
No matter where I am 
And every tear I've cried
You hold in Your hands
You've never left my side
And though my heart is torn
I will praise You in this storm"

I remember when I started my graduate program I felt like a hypocrite. I was educating patients about being healthy and losing weight, when I myself was obese. Obesity is now the #1 epidemic in the world. Yes, an epidemic. Did you know that by simply losing 10% of your body weight it can aide in the help of reducing blood pressure, cholesterol, and controlling type 2 diabetes? Of course, genetics and other health factors play into it differently for everyone. As well as everyone's body is different. So consulting your doctor is best. But even making a goal of 10% seems more manageable than "losing 80 pounds" Start with small goals. Weekly goals. You will be surprised at how much easier your weight loss journey will be. This morning I logged onto social media and something caught my eye. A photographer has made a name for themselves by doing trash the dress sessions for a women celebrating their divorces. It has over 40k shares and my mind is completely blown. I won't mention the quality of said photos (or lack there of) but it has made her an overnight hit. My heart sank as I scrolled through those images. As everyone laughed and cheered her on my heart broke for the love that once was and now is no more. 
I chose to specialize in Weddings and Couples a while back because I love love and all that it stands for. I respect the vows people make at the alter and believe in marriage whole heartedly. I know it can work but only if we are willing to put in work as well. As fun as the wedding is, as beautiful as the bride always looks & as much as I enjoy taking the photos on such a special day, it all pales in comparison to the union that is made and the new life that begins

I don't believe divorce is ever something to celebrate. I would never judge those who have been divorced because I know so many who have and I can't begin to imagine the pain and hurt that comes with waking through that. However, as someone (who has been there) said to me so graciously today "there is NOTHING to celebrate about it only lessons to be learned, wisdom to be gained & mistakes not to be made again." I'm all for bridal sessions and even fun "trash" the dress sessions but only in a way that honors the vow and promise of marriage. So just incase anyone was wondering, no I will not photograph you setting flame to your wedding dress as you tear up photos of your ex. Some trends should stop before they ever got started.

Here is our answer: 
Unlike a full-service event planner, a day of coordinator is for those who wish to plan their own event, but when the event day comes, they need a professional to facilitate the execution of all their hard work in preparation. It is essentially the passing of the baton on the final lap of the event race to ensure a win at the finish line. A day of coordinator takes your vision, preparation, and plans, then implaments them so that all aspects of the wedding are seamless, stress, and worry free.
â
â
More often, well meaning planners rely on family and or friends to help carry out plans on the day of their wedding. In most cases the âvolunteerâ help have little experience in the overall production of the full wedding to ensure the entirety of the day runs smoothly, though they may be great playing a role in part of the production, but not to the full capacity a wedding requires. By asking family or friends to take on the stressful task, those people will not be able to enjoy the wedding as a guest, and will end up feeling like âstaffâ rather than an honored guest. The last thing you want is for family/friends to look back on your special wedding day and remember being stressed and worked, but instead remember the joy and delight in getting to participate in the event along with you. Most importantly, it is the peace of mind that all aspects of your special day are attended to, allowing you to take in every moment of a day that is meant to be remembered for a lifetime! #weddingplanning #bride #sandiegoevents #sandiegowedding #dayofcoordinator #coordinator #weddingcoordinator #linensandlaceweddings #bridetobe #engaged #wedding #weddings

My married friends where you at?

Do you pray for your marriage?  Whether its perfect?  Broken?  Needs some help? I do not really pray as I was taught while growing up, but my wife says she does and well she prays for both of us...But I am willing to do the same and know she will appreciate this.

Marriage is a gift â an amazing blessing from God.  Yet often, the greatest gifts in life are not always cherished the way they should be.  Maybe because life gets busy, or we get hurried and distracted.  Maybe because we start to take one another for granted.  Or we disagree and let resentments hang on longer than they should.

In all of the talk about marriage, defending our views, or pointing out differences, we have to ask ourselves one question... are we working as hard on our marriage, as we do at our jobs?
Life gets hard and we sometimes feel as if we are alone!

I invite you to join me and a group of other spouses to a 31 day challenge to pray for our marriages. Yes, I said pray! ð

The group Starts today Monday, June 6th Comment below if you want in and I will make sure to add you to our Secret/private group!

I am not exaggerating when I say Kamil and Dominika are my soul mates. My soulmates? Yes, that's not a typo! Of course they're each there's soulmates, just look at this picture! But what I mean is that I am entirely in love with them - as individuals, as a couple, as humans. I feel like we've been friends forever. It's a magical thing to capture the wedding of a couple whose hearts and minds are made the same as yours. Working with them felt nothing like work and everything like breathing. When you hire a wedding photographer, that's what you should look for - I want to work with my soul sisters and hug and cry and dance with you on your day. I definitely did all of those things on Saturday.

The weather people keep telling us itâs only going to get worse before it gets better so weâre just going to keep rolling with the punches âð¼ï¸ððªð½ But in all seriousness it breaks my heart to see our couple looking defeated at vicious weather raining on their parade, worrying about whether theyâre actually going to get any photos for their day. âRain on your wedding day is good luckâ they keep being told, and I hated the idea of them thinking that is simply a consoling reassurance, a commiseration of sorts. Rather than avoid the rain we wanted them to have something that reflected their day (and maybe have a laugh at how crazy it all was years later) so managed to convince them to sneak out mid reception for this photo. 
The ongoing Sydney storms unleashed a particularly bad one that day and through no fault of their own, the estate we were on came under a black out. This basically meant no power - no heating for the reception area, no light, no electricity. What was so amazing was how people banded together, determined NOT to let this sully Sarah and Nicâs wedding day.

Massive props to the @malibraefarm team: Greg and Shelly pulled out all stops and went above and beyond to create an incredible day for Sarah and Nic. 
@violetsandvinegar: these awesome guys from the kitchen - without power - fought everything and came back with a gorgeous feast for the entire wedding. 
Both of these teams they did such wonderful work against adversity with so much cheer and grace. 
And finally to Sarah, Nic and their wonderful guests - for carrying so much great humour and continuing to have a magical day regardless of circumstances. Thank you â¤ï¸

The first time I ever talked about marrying @bonesou  was to our mutual friend Scotty two weeks before we even started dating. At that point we were both stuck in miserable parasitic relationships but dreaming of a better future. Two weeks later we were on our first date the same day I broke up with my ex and two days after he left his (I have no balls,  the dude kept crying when I tried previously and I felt bad lmao). Of course he brings up how psycho I am for already planning our wedding.  I told him he'd see. Now,  a little over a year later he's down on one knee in our tent asking me to "keep killing it with him for life" and I'm the happiest girl in the entire world. People will say we're rushing,  but we saved each other and honestly we fight sometimes and we stress and get crazy but never once have either of us doubted that we really have found something incredibly special. When you find your soul mate,  you know it and you don't let go. Thank you Mitch, for promising to take care of me and letting me take care of you for the rest of our lives. #rainbowmoonstone #wedding #engaged #shrublove #nelsonledges #nlqp #happypost

Nobody in the whole wide world will ever understand just how happy this person right here makes me. I try so hard to protect him because I know last time we tried this we hurt each other and nobody thought either of us would make it. I know that my mom stayed up with me for weeks making sure she wouldn't wake up and see me gone. I stayed up talking to her. It too me a long time to feel ok again but always felt empty and alone without her. I'd walk out of my house and want run to hers. Little did I know that she was with her dad. Far away from me. Then one night she was talking to me. Text in me just to say hey. I was freaking out wanting her to know just how I really felt. I was on younow and she was in the phone with me. That night we were back together and truely happy. Restarting this crazy thing called love. We grew a lot away from this stupid thing called high school and became so so strong. I will always love her and fight for her. She is my forever ever and always love story and I will never give that up for anybody. I'm posting this picture of my beautiful fiancÃ©e(!!) from our adventure last week because today marks one year since she left for Wisconsin, beginning our long-distance journey together. And what a journey it's been!

Long distance is hard, there's no denying that. The physical affection and connections that we both long for and love become impossible. But that very fact has forced us to discover new ways to show our love for each other, grow as individuals, be more intentional, savor every moment we get to spend together, and so much more.

God has strengthened us in ways we never expected, ways which we never would have experienced otherwise. We couldn't do this without Him. But with Him, I can say with confidence that we are closer than ever before, despite the distance!

I am so blessed and thankful to have a woman as loving and thoughtful and inspiring and encouraging as Connilyn is.

I know, I know, this is all quite mushy, but I can't help it! I'm so in love. â¤ï¸ One more year, my precious Rose!

Another chance to breath... just gimme a second to share a word. A wedding is an event...but marriage is a life. I know a couple whose wedding lasted longer than their marriage. 
Love in  marriage is more than just a feeling or an emotion. It is a choice.  Love is a decision u refresh everyday with regard to ur spouse. When u wake up in  the morning throughout the day till night, u are choosing a continually to love that man or woman u married. 
Be open to corrections. Being open means making ourselves vulnerable & many people are not willing to do that. Be an exception. U are the Head of the family,  but don't make a mistake, Headship is not Rulership. It is leadership. 
As head u are to provide spiritual leadership & direction to the family through ur words, lifestyle &personal Behaviour 
We are a sum total of what we have learned from all who have taught us, both great & small. Success not only in marriage but in anything else, is not what we have achieved in comparison to what the next man has achieved.

You are not her Boss!! U are her partner!! Work together!! Share the same Vision till death. 
#Respect #humbleness
#engaged #leadership.

On our 3 year anniversary, Cliff surprised me with a dining in the dark experience. Once we finished our sixth course, we were asked if the kitchen trainees could observe the experience for an extra course... I said ok.... Why not, the food was amazing and an extra course wouldn't hurt... ð As we heard people entering into our private pitch black dining room, I wondered why there were so many people coming to observe. I actually laughed and thought maybe there's a twist to this dinner where they show you trying to eat in the dark to the crowd. I was completely caught off guard, a bit blinded and in awe, once the chef turned the lights on and I sort of saw my family and some of my closest friends there. While I was trying to regain my vision and understand what was going on, Cliff got up, said a few words, and thanked everyone for being there. He then proceeded to get down on one knee and asked me to marry him. I sat there with a goofy smile, in complete shock and wonderfully surprised, then said Yes! I proceeded to say thank you for my beautiful ring!ð It was a surreal experience at the moment and a perfect surprise. I couldn't believe how he and my family pulled it off. I am blessed and thankful to have so much love in my life and I am excited Cliff was able to invite some of my dearest family and friends to share this moment with us.ððððEngagement 2016!!!! â¤ï¸#myproposal #mylove #hallmark #fiancÃ© #miami #engaged

So last week some of the best celebrants in Australia (and 1 kiwi) got together to discuss how we can change future brides & grooms perception of ceremony. Our philosophy is that the ceremony should be the prelude to the party not the droll part that's stale and boring. Let's face it, the ceremony is the most important part of the day and without a fabulous celebrant to bring it home for you, it won't be  the most memorable moment that it should be. The best thing is this little group has been together now for 2 years and we all met in person for the first time last week. We always have each other's back and love one another's guts. On that note we are there to support ALL celebrants outside of this posse. Love and peace to the wedding world xx

And I write a letter wishing that you read my feelings. Iknow I was not good and what I've done seems to be unforgivable in your eyes.
But we both know that our hearts were beating as one that day, even when our heads were telling us that it was not right. 
And maybe it seems to be not possible because you are far away but my memorie brings you really close that I almost can feel you.
And after to many mornings without your breath on my neck, I'm still waiting for something that seems to be just a dream.
Many times I ask myself if it really happened. And many times i wonder if I should give up and love who loves me back but that would be just a big lie.
And no, I'm not ok this feeling in my chest of being empty, uncompleted is eating my force and I can't be brave anymore.
Your bright sight leaves me naked, vulnerable, full of fears I thought don't belong to me.
And I wish so much go back in time to thay cold night with only your warmth body as a shelter, that view of #berlin and that bittersweet feeling of being complete for last time.
1 night was enough for you to drive me crazy
And 1 night was enough for me to change your opinion about love.
So let all this behind and let's start over again.

2014 was a pivotal year for me. It's when I really started to walk in authority with who God created me to be. 
It's when I found myself in a relationship that depleted any worth I thought I had left.

After that terrible breakup: I was reborn. Not only in my purity but in my worth. I was restored. I was on the journey to becoming healed. He saved me... again and again. 
I got this tattoo shortly after the breakup because I knew I was stronger. I wanted to be. I had to be. Reading through proverbs 31 gave me courage and wisdom into the eyes of who God was creating me to be.

Today is a very special day for this girl. Today she turns 11 years old, and I can't really believe it! As I was getting ready for the day+her party this morning, she looked at me and told me that I didn't need any make up today. That I was beautiful without it, just like her! I was a little surprised at her comment, but I got to thinking... I go bare faced quite often when I'm just at home, or going to the grocery store, but anywhere I go where I see people I know, I have makeup on. And why? I've never asked myself that question before. I couldn't really think of a reason other than the fact that I feel self conscious without it on my face. I feel unworthy to be seen by people! How silly is that? The Lord made us all in His image, and that is beautiful. So, with the confidence instilled in me by a brand new 11 year old, bare faced I went. We even took a little bare-faced selfie over on my snapchat to commemorate the occasion! I think we can all learn something about inner beauty from this girl. Happy Birthday, Kadie J! You radiate joy, and I am so blessed to be your big sister!

My hubby to be and I have known each other since I was 14 years old and he was 17. We became the best of friends and began dating when I was a senior in high school. He was my first boyfriend and I was his first girlfriend. It's been an amazing 12 years together. We've stuck it through the hard times and been happy through the best of times. He proposed to me in May 2015 by the Hudson River, at the same exact spot we had our first date 12 years ago. That morning, he went to ask my parents for my hand in marriage, which was the sweetest thing to keep up with tradition. I feel like the luckiest girl to have been able to share half of my life with him and soon enough share the rest of my life with him. Sometimes I fall in love with the darkness. The way it lets me settle for negativity, wallow in self pity, find every excuse to quit instead of rise. 
But then I start to feel it. Certain corners of my heart or thoughts in my mind feeling heavier and darker and colder. My feelings towards others get blanketed with annoyance or contempt. My thoughts towards myself breeding lie after lie after lie. 
And then I remember the light. The way it exposes me, calls me to get up, and gives me the strength to do so. Speaks words of truth and empowerment. Reminds me of my value and my place. 
I don't know why I felt led to mention the struggle between finding comfort in the darkness rather than striving towards the light. It may not be specifically a topic for brides. But I do think it's a part of life, to just want to hide in the shadows sometimes. And it did happen to me when I was a bride. It's easy to slip into an intimacy with the darkness at any point in your life really, if you let your guard down. 
I urge you to think of the moments that you've lived lightly in the sun and how much sweeter that life is. You can get back there. 
The first thing you have to do is look over in that direction. Stop turning back to your self pity or bitterness or drama for comfort. Face the light. See what it has to offer. â¨

I don't know that I've ever described a photo shoot as magical.  But yesterday... there are no other words.  The women of the #Crossfit gym that I go to decided to plan a "#PinUp" styled #photoshoot.  It was just supposed to be for fun, something to do together, but honestly it was so much more than that.  As usual, with everything crossfit, it turned into all of us cheering each other on as we lifted really heavy things, tried new crazy gymnastics movements and, well, took tops off.  We all had different reasons for doing it, as was expressed by the t's that were worn: "I'm 40 b*****es" or "Unf****withable". Some went full 50's glamour pin up and some went back to their roots with #pointe shoes and #ballerina skirts.  But every single woman that was there was built up and repeatedly told how awesome they looked.  Every single one laughed uncontrollably at one point during their photos.  We had an UNBELIEVABLE time, and our bond is even stronger now than it was (if possible). Hopefully every @crossfit_inguz Lady will be able to make it next time, because it truly was something special.

Daily #tarotreading for June 5: Knight of Cups
Are you feeling romantic, dreamy, willing to be open and vulnerable in order to get your message across? Or are you being approached by a "white knight" with such an invitation? Perhaps even one on bended knee? Then you are swept off your feet by the sweet enthusiasm of the Knight of Cups. This Knight of Cups is in touch with his feelings and intuition - he's romantic, charming, and even poetic at times. He may demonstrate his devotion through silver-tongued speeches, art, or another form of creativity, and he's willing to bare it all in the name of love - or, in his negative aspect, the fantasy of it. Knights are "young" in the Tarot, whatever the age of the person they may represent - they still have some maturing to do, and at his lowest, the Knight of Cups can get moody, emotionally unstable, lost in dreams or regrets. But generally, the Knight of Cups represents an event in our lives, or a person, that invites us to open ourselves up to love, to possibility, and to courageously feeling the heights and depths that come with them...

All day everyday. If I said it wasn't hard, if I told you I looked forward to every workout, every cardio session... I'd be lying. This isn't a sport for everyone. Some don't even give it credit as being a sport. How do I do it? That's my favorite question... I put on my music or my motivational videos and handle it. Do you offer discounts? 
No, at Bellissima we pride ourselves on offering the best price possible to our brides. We work closely with our designers and respect their required pricing. If you find a salon that does offer discounting many times they are marking the gown up so they can offer a discount. It is a sales tactic that Bellissima does not believe in. We want our brides to find their gown in a no pressure lovely setting! Once or twice a year we host Sample Sales and Designer Trunk Shows. During these times trunk show incentives maybe available. This is why Trunk Shows book up quickly! There are benefits to being a Bellissima Bride! We do offer our brides specials on Bridesmaids dresses and other accessories. We give each bride an amazing gift bag and make sure all our brides are happy through the wedding day! #bellissima #q&a #questions #questionsandanswers #southernbride #southerncharm #carolinabride #winstonsalem #ncbride #carolinabride #engaged #bridetobe #appointmentsavailable

Have you ever looked at a photograph from the past when you were little? Of course you have. You've made fun of how your mom dressed you, your parents' crazy huge glasses, the weird tile in the kitchen in the house you grew up in. When I look at photos it brings back so many memories, both happy and sad. It's made me realize how thankful I am that someone took that picture. 25 years ago those moments must have been photo worthy because my mom had to whip out the film camera, hope it turned out, then develop the film at the store (definitely not instant gratification). Even after 4 years, I still second guess myself and ask "What am I doing?" So, what am I doing? This. Taking photos so 25 years from now, someone will be flipping through a photo album, running through memories in their mind as they turn the pages of that book.  This is why I love my job. #lindseyyeagleyphoto 
PS. Oldie but a goodie of little Trevor!

I don't know whhhhhy I do this to myself. I'm always seem to be awake super late before work trips (with early morning flights). Before I go to bed, a flood of tasks and reminders are remembered and they all of a sudden pile up.

Does anyone else try to cram in everything before they leave?! Should we start a club? I need my husband to know I'm not the only crazy person who does this!

3 suitcases for 3 different trips. Then I come home for one day and I'll need to pack 2 more suitcases for 2 different trips. 
This month I'll be in Houston, San Diego, Pismo (for a family trip/memorial), back to San Diego, up to San Jose, and then ending the month back in San Diego. I am at home for only 4 days this entire month! Holy smokes!! Speaking of smoke, how amazing is this picture? These wedding photos are seriously amazing!

Thanks for reading my mini novel. I am tired, thankful, excited, and looking forward to the many, many sneak peeks ahead!

Tricia + Ruobing, Established 5.28.16 with a grand celebration steeped in tradition.

The lion dance is a traditional Chinese dance performed on big occasions, such as the Spring Festival (Chinese New Year) for good luck, as it is believed that the lion is an auspicious animal. 
Performed in a lion costume, accompanied by the music of beating drums, clashing cymbals, and resounding gongs, lion dances imitate a lion's various movements or demonstrate martial arts agility, depending on the style.

The Origin and History of Lion Dances
Opinions about the origin of the lion dance are widely divided. The most reliable one is this:

In traditional Chinese culture, the lion, like the Chinese dragon, was only an animal which existed in myth, and there were no actual lions in China. Before the Han Dynasty (202 BC â 220 AD), only a few lions had reached the Central Plains from the western area of ancient China (now Xinjiang), due to Silk Road trade.

At that time, people mimicked the appearance and actions of the newly arrived lions in a performance, which developed into the lion dance in the Three Kingdoms Period (220â280) and then became popular with the rise of Buddhism in the Northern and Southern Dynasties (420â589). In the Tang Dynasty (618â907), the lion dance was one of the court dances.

After that lion dances continued to become a popular performance among the people, to pray for good luck during the Spring Festival or during other celebrations, such as Tricia and Ruobing's wedding day! #wukingclan
